N o. 3
Commercial Agency 
at Sierra Leone Mah 30th 1841

Sir,
I have the honor to acknwledge receipt  of dispatch No 14 dated Febry 21 1871 conferring upon me the appointment of Vice Commercial Agent of the United States at this port which I hereby have the honor to accept. 

The <unclear/> effects of the climate on my health compels me to leave soon for Ameria when with the sanction of the Department I purpose remainingn a short time when the necesary bond will be expected.

I have the honor to be 
Your Obdt Servt
J.B. Upton
U.S. Vice Comm Agent

To the honorable
Secretary of State
Washington
D.C

